</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[533,1528,693,1306]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[565,669,970,994]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks:</emphasis>
The species was first recorded in Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[1146,1240,970,994]" name="Malaysia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
as a new subspecies, 
<emphasis box="[1463,1486,971,994]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1499,1517,971,994]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">w</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[533,622,1005,1029]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">albicollis</emphasis>
in Pasoh Forest Reserve [
<bibRefCitation author="Francis CM" box="[895,920,1005,1029]" journalOrPublisher="Can J Zool." pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="2878 - 2282" part="67" refId="ref41456" refString="84. Francis CM. Notes on fruit bats (Chiroptera, Pteropodidae) from Malaysia and Brunei, with the description of a new subspecies of Megaerops wetmorei Taylor, 1934. Can J Zool. 1989; 67 (12): 2878 - 2282." title="Notes on fruit bats (Chiroptera, Pteropodidae) from Malaysia and Brunei, with the description of a new subspecies of Megaerops wetmorei Taylor, 1934" type="journal article" year="1989">84</bibRefCitation>
] with distinctive white tufts on the shoulders and neck [
<bibRefCitation author="Kingston T &amp; Lim BL &amp; Akbar Z." box="[542,567,1040,1064]" journalOrPublisher="Penerbit Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref38130" refString="11. Kingston T, Lim BL, Akbar Z. Bats of Krau wildlife reserve. Penerbit Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia; 2006." title="Bats of Krau wildlife reserve" type="book" year="2006">11</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Francis CM" box="[580,605,1040,1064]" journalOrPublisher="Can J Zool." pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="2878 - 2282" part="67" refId="ref41456" refString="84. Francis CM. Notes on fruit bats (Chiroptera, Pteropodidae) from Malaysia and Brunei, with the description of a new subspecies of Megaerops wetmorei Taylor, 1934. Can J Zool. 1989; 67 (12): 2878 - 2282." title="Notes on fruit bats (Chiroptera, Pteropodidae) from Malaysia and Brunei, with the description of a new subspecies of Megaerops wetmorei Taylor, 1934" type="journal article" year="1989">84</bibRefCitation>
]. The 
<typeStatus box="[674,719,1040,1064]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Taylor" authorityYear="1934" box="[752,883,1040,1064]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Megaerops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wetmorei">
<emphasis box="[752,775,1040,1063]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[787,883,1040,1063]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">wetmorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<bibRefCitation author="Taylor EH" box="[898,923,1040,1064]" journalOrPublisher="Bureau of Science, Department of Agriculture and Commerce, Government of the Philippine Islands, Manila" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref41422" refString="83. Taylor EH. Philippine land mammals. Monograph No. 30, Bureau of Science, Department of Agriculture and Commerce, Government of the Philippine Islands, Manila; 1934." title="Philippine land mammals. Monograph" type="book" year="1934">83</bibRefCitation>
] lacked the white neck tufts (which was followed in the description by Corbet and Hill [
<bibRefCitation author="Corbet GB &amp; Hill JE" box="[873,886,1074,1098]" journalOrPublisher="Oxford: Oxford University Press" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref38080" refString="9. Corbet GB, Hill JE. The mammals of the Indomalayan region: a systematic review. Oxford: Oxford University Press; 1992." title="The mammals of the Indomalayan region: a systematic review" type="book" year="1992">9</bibRefCitation>
]) and has a short tail of 1.5 mm [
<bibRefCitation author="Taylor EH" box="[1237,1262,1074,1098]" journalOrPublisher="Bureau of Science, Department of Agriculture and Commerce, Government of the Philippine Islands, Manila" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref41422" refString="83. Taylor EH. Philippine land mammals. Monograph No. 30, Bureau of Science, Department of Agriculture and Commerce, Government of the Philippine Islands, Manila; 1934." title="Philippine land mammals. Monograph" type="book" year="1934">83</bibRefCitation>
]. Specimens of 
<emphasis box="[1430,1453,1075,1098]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1465,1483,1075,1098]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">w</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[533,622,1109,1133]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">albicollis</emphasis>
from Pasoh Forest Reserve have a short tail of ~ 
<quantity box="[1131,1195,1109,1133]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
[
<bibRefCitation author="Francis CM" box="[1210,1235,1109,1133]" journalOrPublisher="Can J Zool." pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="2878 - 2282" part="67" refId="ref41456" refString="84. Francis CM. Notes on fruit bats (Chiroptera, Pteropodidae) from Malaysia and Brunei, with the description of a new subspecies of Megaerops wetmorei Taylor, 1934. Can J Zool. 1989; 67 (12): 2878 - 2282." title="Notes on fruit bats (Chiroptera, Pteropodidae) from Malaysia and Brunei, with the description of a new subspecies of Megaerops wetmorei Taylor, 1934" type="journal article" year="1989">84</bibRefCitation>
] whereas specimens from Krau Wildlife Reserve [
<bibRefCitation author="Kingston T &amp; Lim BL &amp; Akbar Z." box="[782,807,1144,1168]" journalOrPublisher="Penerbit Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refId="ref38130" refString="11. Kingston T, Lim BL, Akbar Z. Bats of Krau wildlife reserve. Penerbit Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia; 2006." title="Bats of Krau wildlife reserve" type="book" year="2006">11</bibRefCitation>
] are tailless. Further analysis, and more DNA barcordes, would be required to determine whether 
<emphasis box="[866,889,1179,1202]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[901,919,1179,1202]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">w</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[930,1019,1178,1202]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">albicollis</emphasis>
deserves to be recognised as a species distinct from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Taylor" authorityYear="1934" box="[592,753,1213,1237]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Megaerops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wetmorei">
<emphasis box="[592,615,1213,1236]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[627,645,1213,1236]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">w</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[657,753,1213,1236]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">wetmorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
